-- The United States will give 350,000 U.S. dollars to a Kenyan project aimed at linking the east African country's universities to the Internet. With the new grant, the Kenya Education Network is expected to connect 20 universities and research facilities to the Internet within a year and 600 primary and secondary schools within three years, Vivian Derryck, assistant administrator of the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) , said in Nairobi  The network was established last year by the Kenyan government and universities, with the support of the country's private sector and the USAID.
